    <exercise number="23"><statement><p>
        <m>f(x)=\dfrac{1}{3}\abs{x} </m>
    </p></statement>
    <answer><p><ol label="a">
        <li><p>Scale factor <m>\frac{1}{3} </m>; <m>y =\abs{x}</m> is compressed vertically by the scale factor.</p></li>
        <li><p><image source="images/fig-ans-2-3-23"  width="45%"><description>transformed absolute value</description></image> </p></li>
    </ol></p></answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise number="24"><statement><p>
        <m>H(x)=-3\abs{x} </m>
    </p></statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise number="25"><statement><p>
        <m>h(z)=\dfrac{-2}{z^2} </m>
    </p></statement>
    <answer><p><ol label="a">
        <li><p>Scale factor <m>-2 </m>; <m>y =\frac{1}{z^2}</m> is reflected over the <m>z</m>-axis and stretched vertically by a factor of <m>2</m>.</p></li>
        <li><p><image source="images/fig-ans-2-3-25"  width="45%"><description>transformed inverse-square</description></image> </p></li>
    </ol></p></answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise number="26"><statement><p>
        <m>g(z)=\dfrac{2}{z} </m>
