<exercisegroup><introduction><p>
    In Problems 35–38, the graph of a function is shown. Describe each transformation of the graph; then give a formula for each in terms of the original function.
</p></introduction>

<exercise number="35"><statement><p>
    <sidebyside width="80%"><image source="images/fig-2-3-35"><description> graph and 4 transformations</description></image> </sidebyside>
</p></statement>
<answer><p><ol label="a">
    <li><p>Vertically stretched by a factor of <m>3</m>: <m>y = 3 f (x)</m></p></li>
    <li><p>Reflected about the <m>x</m>-axis: <m>y = -f (x)</m></p></li>
    <li><p>Translated <m>1</m> unit right: <m>y = f (x - 1)</m></p></li>
    <li><p>Translated <m>4</m> units up: <m>y = f (x) + 4</m></p></li>
</ol></p></answer>
</exercise>

<exercise number="36"><statement><p>
    <sidebyside width="80%"><image source="images/fig-2-3-36"><description> graph and 4 transformations</description></image> </sidebyside>
